issue.title: Precinct

labels.name: concept
labels.description: high level stuff, not things to implement

issue.body:
Anyone can create a precinct
- precincts contain
   - a list of approved officers
   - a list of approved admins

an address has to be an approved officer to add an action

issue.title: Associate addresses with officers

labels.name: concept
labels.description: high level stuff, not things to implement

issue.body:
officers addresses are approved by an admin in a Precinct (issue #1 )

an officer can submit/update:
- name
- badge # 
- title (detective, lab assistant, etc)

issue.title: Evidence

labels.name: concept
labels.description: high level stuff, not things to implement

issue.body:
created with a specific function, by any officer

- who
- what (long form description)
- when
- where
- id num

has an array of actions (#4)

issue.title: Actions

labels.name: concept
labels.description: high level stuff, not things to implement

issue.body:
- who
- what they did (description)
- comments
- action type
  - crime scene, lab test, transport, stored, etc
- result

maybe:
- reason
- image

issue.title: Result

labels.name: concept
labels.description: high level stuff, not things to implement

issue.body:
The outcome of an action, such as a lab test.  May happen later in the timeline of a piece of evidence but is associated with an action in the past.
- who
- where
- when
- comments
- result info

issue.title: Create Precinct flow
issue.body:
- create precinct button appears if the address is not already in a precinct

- has form

- calls stubbed Precinct create function

issue.title: New Precinct Function
issue.body:
Takes:
            newPrecinct Name,
            newPrecinct Address,
            Sherif Name,
            Sherif BadgeNumber,
            Sherif Title,
Does:
add precinct to precinct list, generate precinct id

add sheriff to address->precinctid admin map
add sheriff to address->precinctid actor map
